	Creatures of nature
      </p>
    </monstergroupdescription>
  </monstergroupinfo>

  
  <monster>    
    <monstertitle>Bear</monstertitle>
    <monsterid>animal.bear</monsterid>
    <monstertag>Animal</monstertag>
    <monstermove>8</monstermove>
    <monsterhealth>50</monsterhealth>
    <monsterstamina>20</monsterstamina>
    <monsterinitiativebonus>+2</monsterinitiativebonus>
    <monsterresolve>2d8</monsterresolve>
    <monstermagic>2d6</monstermagic>
    <ac>9</ac>
    <strength>15</strength>
    <endurance>14</endurance>
    <agility>9</agility>
    <speed>14</speed>
    <luck>9</luck>
    <willpower>7</willpower>
    <perception>11</perception>
    <monsterdescription>
      <p>
	Bears are large omniverous mammals who live in forests and the northern steppes.
	They seldom attack humans unless they are startled, very hungry, or protecting
	their young.
      </p>
    </monsterdescription>    
  </monster>


  <monster>    
    <monstertitle>Spider, Giant</monstertitle>
    <monsterid>animal.spider_giant</monsterid>
    <monstertag>Animal</monstertag>
    <monstermove>8</monstermove>
    <monsterhealth>30</monsterhealth>
    <monsterstamina>20</monsterstamina>
    <monsterinitiativebonus>+3</monsterinitiativebonus>
    <monsterresolve>2d8</monsterresolve>
    <monstermagic>3d6</monstermagic>
    <ac>9</ac>
    <strength>16</strength>
    <endurance>14</endurance>
    <agility>11</agility>
    <speed>15</speed>
    <luck>7</luck>
    <willpower>8</willpower>
    <perception>12</perception>    
    <abilitylevelid>monster.poison_bite_2</abilitylevelid>
    <abilitylevelid>monster.web_2</abilitylevelid>
    <monsterdescription>
      <p>
	Giant Spiders get two attacks per round, a web attack and a
	poisonous bite attack.  Spider poison lasts till a short rest.  Fresh poison
	from the spiders corpse is potent for one day after it is sourced.
      </p>

      <p>
	Giant spiders are intelligent.  If they have the upper hand they like
	to taunt their prey.  Wondering aloud how they'll taste, telling them
	they'll make their deaths slow and asking them to choose which one to kill
	first.  They are completely untrusting and untrustworthy creatures.
      </p>
    </monsterdescription>    
  </monster>  
  


  <monster>    
